
## ğŸ¯ Objective
To install and configure Ubuntu on a virtual machine using VMware Workstation.  
This lab helps students understand virtualization and Linux environment setup.

---

## âš™ï¸ Procedure / Steps

1. Download and install VMware Workstation.  
2. Download the Ubuntu ISO file from the official website.  
3. Create a new virtual machine in VMware.  
4. Attach the Ubuntu ISO to the virtual CD/DVD drive.  
5. Start the VM and follow installation prompts.  
6. Configure disk space, username, and password.  
7. Complete installation and log in to Ubuntu.  
8. Test the network by running basic commands like `ping google.com`.

